               <p>I am servant to the prosecutor, who <rs id="t17780429-87-viclabel410" type="occupation">keeps a coffee-house</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17780429-87-victim728 t17780429-87-viclabel410"></join>. The prisoner came into the coffee-house on the 28th of February; he had a tumbler of rum and water and there was a spoon in it. When he went out I missed the spoon; I followed him and brought him back, and I found the spoon wrapped up in a handkerchief in his hand.</p>

               <p>(
               <persName id="t17780429-87-person730">
                  William
                   Marsdell
               <interp inst="t17780429-87-person730" type="surname" value="Marsdell"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17780429-87-person730" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17780429-87-person730" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             produced the spoon, which was deposed to by 
               <persName id="t17780429-87-person731">
                  George
                   Clarke
               <interp inst="t17780429-87-person731" type="surname" value="Clarke"></interp>
